article.headline: Binghamton 79, North Florida 61
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Steve Proctor scored a career-high 26 points and Richard Forbes came off the bench to add 21 to lead Binghamton to a 79-61 win over North Florida on Monday night. Proctor sparked a 14-2 run midway in the first half when he drilled two shots beyond the arc and added four free throws to give the Bearcats (5-4) a 29-15 lead with just under seven minutes left. They led 41-26 at halftime. North Florida (1-9) rallied in the second half to cut the deficit to 50-40 with 14 minutes remaining, but Binghamton responded with a 12-2 surge to open up a 20-point lead, 62-42. The Bearcats led by at least 16 points the rest of the game. Proctor had never scored more than 17 points in his two years with the Bearcats, but he connected on 8-of-12 shots from the floor, all six of his free throw attempts and 4-of-8 3-pointer attempts. He scored 15 points in the first half. Forbes, who leads the Bearcats in scoring despite not having started any of the team's nine games, connected on all five of his field goal attempts and converted 11 of 13 free throws. He scored 15 points in the second half to surpass his season average of 13.6 points per game. Rashad Williams led North Florida with 16 points, while James Grimball had a double-double with 10 points and a game-high 13 rebounds.
